.\" ====================================================================
.SH BUGS
.\" ====================================================================
\fB\-\-transport raw:\fR\fIifname\fR requires the interface to already be
in promiscuous mode or the kernel to have the appropriate socket filter
in place when used with \fB\-\-decode\fR; otherwise only packets
addressed to the host MAC are captured.
.PP
\fB\-\-count 0\fR (unlimited) with \fB\-\-transport verilator:\fR will
fill the DUT\(cqs receive FIFO if the DUT is slower than the generator.
Backpressure is only available in the SystemC integration
.RI ( sim/ ).
